JOHANNESBURG - The Council for Medical Schemes report into allegations of discrimination against black doctors has only increased conversation about the state of private healthcare in South Africa. This week Checkpoint takes a step behind the headlines, into the lives of black medical practitioners who say they’ve suffered due to trumped-up fraud charges by South Africa's largest medical schemes. READ: Racial discrimination: Doctors call for decisive action The section 59 preliminary report has been sent to all medical aids implicated, for a response, before a final report is concluded. All medical aids mentioned in the Checkpoint story declined to be interviewed. For more details watch the full episode here.